/-!
# Definitions about filters in topological spaces

In this file we define filters in topological spaces,
as well as other definitions that rely on `Filter`s.

## Main Definitions

### Neighborhoods filter

* `nhds x`: the filter of neighborhoods of a point in a topological space,
  denoted by `рқ“қ x` in the `Topology` scope.
  A set is called a neighborhood of `x`, if it includes an open set around `x`.

* `nhdsWithin x s`: the filter of neighborhoods of a point within a set,
  defined as `рқ“қ x вҠ“ рқ“ҹ s` and denoted by `рқ“қ[s] x`.
  We also introduce notation for some special sets `s`, see below.

* `nhdsSet s`: the filter of neighborhoods of a set in a topological space,
  denoted by `рқ“қЛў s` in the `Topology` scope.
  A set `t` is called a neighborhood of `s`, if it includes an open set that includes `s`.

* `nhdsSetWithin s t`: the filter of neighborhoods of a set `s` within another set `t`,
  defined as `рқ“қЛў s вҠ“ рқ“ҹ t` and denoted by `рқ“қЛў[t] s` in the `Topology` scope.

* `nhdsKer s`: The *neighborhoods kernel* of a set is the intersection of all its neighborhoods.
  In an Alexandrov-discrete space, this is the smallest neighborhood of the set.

  Note that this construction is unnamed in the literature.
  We choose the name in analogy to `interior`.

### Continuity at a point

* `ContinuousAt f x`: a function `f` is continuous at a point `x`,
  if it tends to `рқ“қ (f x)` along `рқ“қ x`.

* `ContinuousWithinAt f s x`: a function `f` is continuous within a set `s` at a point `x`,
  if it tends to `рқ“қ (f x)` along `рқ“қ[s] x`.

* `ContinuousOn f s`: a function `f : X вҶ’ Y` is continuous on a set `s`,
  if it is continuous within `s` at every point of `s`.

### Limits

* `lim f`: a limit of a filter `f` in a nonempty topological space.
  If there exists `x` such that `f вүӨ рқ“қ x`, then `lim f` is one of such points,
  otherwise it is `Classical.choice _`.

  In a Hausdorff topological space, the limit is unique if it exists.

* `Ultrafilter.lim f`: a limit of an ultrafilter `f`,
  defined as the limit of `(f : Filter X)`
  with a proof of `Nonempty X` deduced from existence of an ultrafilter on `X`.

* `limUnder f g`: a limit of a filter `f` along a function `g`, defined as `lim (Filter.map g f)`.

### Cluster points and accumulation points

* `ClusterPt x F`: a point `x` is a *cluster point* of a filter `F`,
  if `рқ“қ x` is not disjoint with `F`.

* `MapClusterPt x F u`: a point `x` is a *cluster point* of a function `u` along a filter `F`,
  if it is a cluster point of the filter `Filter.map u F`.

* `AccPt x F`: a point `x` is an *accumulation point* of a filter `F`,
  if `рқ“қ[вү ] x` is not disjoint with `F`.
  Every accumulation point of a filter is its cluster point, but not vice versa.

* `IsCompact s`: a set `s` is compact if for every nontrivial filter `f` that contains `s`,
  there exists `a вҲҲ s` such that every set of `f` meets every neighborhood of `a`.
  Equivalently, a set `s` is compact if for any cover of `s` by open sets,
  there exists a finite subcover.

* `CompactSpace`, `NoncompactSpace`: typeclasses saying that the whole space
  is a compact set / is not a compact set, respectively.

* `WeaklyLocallyCompactSpace X`: typeclass saying that every point of `X`
  has a compact neighborhood.

* `LocallyCompactSpace X`: typeclass saying that every point of `X`
  has a basis of compact neighborhoods.
  Every locally compact space is a weakly locally compact space.
  The reverse implication is true for RвӮҒ (preregular) spaces.

* `LocallyCompactPair X Y`: an auxiliary typeclass saying that
  for any continuous function `f : X вҶ’ Y`, a point `x`, and a neighborhood `s` of `f x`,
  there exists a compact neighborhood `K` of `x` such that `f` maps `K` to `s`.

* `Filter.cocompact`, `Filter.coclosedCompact`:
  filters generated by complements to compact and closed compact sets, respectively.

## Notation

* `рқ“қ x`: the filter `nhds x` of neighborhoods of a point `x`;
* `рқ“ҹ s`: the principal filter of a set `s`, defined elsewhere;
* `рқ“қ[s] x`: the filter `nhdsWithin x s` of neighborhoods of a point `x` within a set `s`;
* `рқ“қ[вүӨ] x`: the filter `nhdsWithin x (Set.Iic x)` of left-neighborhoods of `x`;
* `рқ“қ[вүҘ] x`: the filter `nhdsWithin x (Set.Ici x)` of right-neighborhoods of `x`;
* `рқ“қ[<] x`: the filter `nhdsWithin x (Set.Iio x)` of punctured left-neighborhoods of `x`;
* `рқ“қ[>] x`: the filter `nhdsWithin x (Set.Ioi x)` of punctured right-neighborhoods of `x`;
* `рқ“қ[вү ] x`: the filter `nhdsWithin x {x}б¶ң` of punctured neighborhoods of `x`;
* `рқ“қЛў s`: the filter `nhdsSet s` of neighborhoods of a set.
-/

@[expose] public section

assert_not_exists Ultrafilter

variable {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]

open Filter
open scoped Topology

/-- A set is called a neighborhood of `x` if it contains an open set around `x`. The set of all
neighborhoods of `x` forms a filter, the neighborhood filter at `x`, is here defined as the
infimum over the principal filters of all open sets containing `x`. -/
irreducible_def nhds (x : X) : Filter X :=
  вЁ… s вҲҲ { s : Set X | x вҲҲ s вҲ§ IsOpen s }, рқ“ҹ s

@[inherit_doc]
scoped[Topology] notation "рқ“қ" => nhds

/-- The "neighborhood within" filter. Elements of `рқ“қ[s] x` are sets containing the
intersection of `s` and a neighborhood of `x`. -/
def nhdsWithin (x : X) (s : Set X) : Filter X :=
  рқ“қ x вҠ“ рқ“ҹ s

@[inherit_doc]
scoped[Topology] notation "рқ“қ[" s "] " x:100 => nhdsWithin x s

/-- Notation for the filter of punctured neighborhoods of a point. -/
scoped[Topology] notation3 (name := nhdsNE) "рқ“қ[вү ] " x:100 =>
  nhdsWithin x (@singleton _ (Set _) Set.instSingletonSet x)б¶ң

/-- Notation for the filter of right neighborhoods of a point. -/
scoped[Topology] notation3 (name := nhdsGE) "рқ“қ[вүҘ] " x:100 => nhdsWithin x (Set.Ici x)

/-- Notation for the filter of left neighborhoods of a point. -/
scoped[Topology] notation3 (name := nhdsLE) "рқ“қ[вүӨ] " x:100 => nhdsWithin x (Set.Iic x)

/-- Notation for the filter of punctured right neighborhoods of a point. -/
scoped[Topology] notation3 (name := nhdsGT) "рқ“қ[>] " x:100 => nhdsWithin x (Set.Ioi x)

/-- Notation for the filter of punctured left neighborhoods of a point. -/
scoped[Topology] notation3 (name := nhdsLT) "рқ“қ[<] " x:100 => nhdsWithin x (Set.Iio x)

/-- The filter of neighborhoods of a set in a topological space. -/
def nhdsSet (s : Set X) : Filter X :=
  sSup (nhds '' s)

@[inherit_doc] scoped[Topology] notation "рқ“қЛў" => nhdsSet

/-- The "neighbourhood within" filter for sets. Elements of `рқ“қ[t] s` are sets containing the
intersection of `t` and a neighbourhood of `s`. -/
def nhdsSetWithin (s t : Set X) : Filter X := рқ“қЛў s вҠ“ рқ“ҹ t

@[inherit_doc] scoped[Topology] notation "рқ“қЛў[" t "] " s:100 => nhdsSetWithin s t

/-- The *neighborhoods kernel* of a set is the intersection of all its neighborhoods. In an
Alexandrov-discrete space, this is the smallest neighborhood of the set. -/
def nhdsKer (s : Set X) : Set X := (рқ“қЛў s).ker

/-- A function between topological spaces is continuous at a point `xвӮҖ`
if `f x` tends to `f xвӮҖ` when `x` tends to `xвӮҖ`. -/
@[fun_prop]
def ContinuousAt (f : X вҶ’ Y) (x : X) :=
  Tendsto f (рқ“қ x) (рқ“қ (f x))

/-- A function between topological spaces is continuous at a point `xвӮҖ` within a subset `s`
if `f x` tends to `f xвӮҖ` when `x` tends to `xвӮҖ` while staying within `s`. -/
@[fun_prop]
def ContinuousWithinAt (f : X вҶ’ Y) (s : Set X) (x : X) : Prop :=
  Tendsto f (рқ“қ[s] x) (рқ“қ (f x))

/-- A function between topological spaces is continuous on a subset `s`
when it's continuous at every point of `s` within `s`. -/
@[fun_prop]
def ContinuousOn (f : X вҶ’ Y) (s : Set X) : Prop :=
  вҲҖ x вҲҲ s, ContinuousWithinAt f s x

/-- `x` specializes to `y` (notation: `x вӨі y`) if either of the following equivalent properties
hold:

* `рқ“қ x вүӨ рқ“қ y`; this property is used as the definition;
* `pure x вүӨ рқ“қ y`; in other words, any neighbourhood of `y` contains `x`;
* `y вҲҲ closure {x}`;
* `closure {y} вҠҶ closure {x}`;
* for any closed set `s` we have `x вҲҲ s вҶ’ y вҲҲ s`;
* for any open set `s` we have `y вҲҲ s вҶ’ x вҲҲ s`;
* `y` is a cluster point of the filter `pure x = рқ“ҹ {x}`.

This relation defines a `Preorder` on `X`. If `X` is a TвӮҖ space, then this preorder is a partial
order. If `X` is a TвӮҒ space, then this partial order is trivial : `x вӨі y вҶ” x = y`. -/
def Specializes (x y : X) : Prop := рқ“қ x вүӨ рқ“қ y

@[inherit_doc]
infixl:300 " вӨі " => Specializes

/-- Two points `x` and `y` in a topological space are `Inseparable`, or *topologically
indistinguishable*, if any of the following equivalent properties hold:

- `рқ“қ x = рқ“қ y`; we use this property as the definition;
- for any open set `s`, `x вҲҲ s вҶ” y вҲҲ s`, see `inseparable_iff_forall_isOpen`;
- for any closed set `s`, `x вҲҲ s вҶ” y вҲҲ s`, see `inseparable_iff_forall_isClosed`;
- `x вҲҲ closure {y}` and `y вҲҲ closure {x}`, see `inseparable_iff_mem_closure`;
- `closure {x} = closure {y}`, see `inseparable_iff_closure_eq`.
-/
def Inseparable (x y : X) : Prop :=
  рқ“қ x = рқ“қ y

variable (X)

/-- Specialization forms a preorder on the topological space. -/
@[instance_reducible]
def specializationPreorder : Preorder X :=
  { Preorder.lift (OrderDual.toDual вҲҳ рқ“қ) with
    le := fun x y => y вӨі x
    lt := fun x y => y вӨі x вҲ§ В¬x вӨі y }

/-- A `setoid` version of `Inseparable`, used to define the `SeparationQuotient`. -/
@[implicit_reducible]
def inseparableSetoid : Setoid X := { Setoid.comap рқ“қ вҠҘ with r := Inseparable }

/-- The quotient of a topological space by its `inseparableSetoid`. Also called the Kolmogorov
quotient. This quotient is guaranteed to be a TвӮҖ space. -/
def SeparationQuotient := Quotient (inseparableSetoid X)

variable {X}

section Lim


/-- If `f` is a filter, then `Filter.lim f` is a limit of the filter, if it exists. -/
noncomputable def Filter.lim [Nonempty X] (f : Filter X) : X :=
  Classical.epsilon fun x => f вүӨ рқ“қ x

@[deprecated (since := "2026-03-12")] alias lim := Filter.lim

/-- If `f` is a filter in `Оұ` and `g : Оұ вҶ’ X` is a function, then `Filter.limUnder f g` is a limit
of `g` at `f`, if it exists. -/
noncomputable def Filter.limUnder {Оұ : Type*} [Nonempty X] (f : Filter Оұ) (g : Оұ вҶ’ X) : X :=
  lim (f.map g)

@[deprecated (since := "2026-03-12")] alias limUnder := Filter.limUnder

end Lim

/-- A point `x` is a cluster point of a filter `F` if `рқ“қ x вҠ“ F вү  вҠҘ`.
Also known as an accumulation point or a limit point, but beware that terminology varies.
This is *not* the same as asking `рқ“қ[вү ] x вҠ“ F вү  вҠҘ`, which is called `AccPt` in Mathlib.
See `mem_closure_iff_clusterPt` in particular. -/
def ClusterPt (x : X) (F : Filter X) : Prop :=
  NeBot (рқ“қ x вҠ“ F)

/-- A point `x` is a cluster point of a sequence `u` along a filter `F` if it is a cluster point
of `map u F`. -/
def MapClusterPt {О№ : Type*} (x : X) (F : Filter О№) (u : О№ вҶ’ X) : Prop :=
  ClusterPt x (map u F)

/-- A point `x` is an accumulation point of a filter `F` if `рқ“қ[вү ] x вҠ“ F вү  вҠҘ`.
See also `ClusterPt`. -/
def AccPt (x : X) (F : Filter X) : Prop :=
  NeBot (рқ“қ[вү ] x вҠ“ F)

/-- A set `s` is compact if for every nontrivial filter `f` that contains `s`,
there exists `a вҲҲ s` such that every set of `f` meets every neighborhood of `a`. -/
def IsCompact (s : Set X) :=
  вҲҖ вҰғfвҰ„ [NeBot f], f вүӨ рқ“ҹ s вҶ’ вҲғ x вҲҲ s, ClusterPt x f

variable (X) in
/-- Type class for compact spaces. Separation is sometimes included in the definition, especially
in the French literature, but we do not include it here. -/
class CompactSpace : Prop where
  /-- In a compact space, `Set.univ` is a compact set. -/
  isCompact_univ : IsCompact (Set.univ : Set X)

variable (X) in
/-- `X` is a noncompact topological space if it is not a compact space. -/
class NoncompactSpace : Prop where
  /-- In a noncompact space, `Set.univ` is not a compact set. -/
  noncompact_univ : В¬IsCompact (Set.univ : Set X)

/-- We say that a topological space is a *weakly locally compact space*,
if each point of this space admits a compact neighborhood. -/
class WeaklyLocallyCompactSpace (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] : Prop where
  /-- Every point of a weakly locally compact space admits a compact neighborhood. -/
  exists_compact_mem_nhds (x : X) : вҲғ s, IsCompact s вҲ§ s вҲҲ рқ“қ x

export WeaklyLocallyCompactSpace (exists_compact_mem_nhds)

/-- There are various definitions of "locally compact space" in the literature,
which agree for Hausdorff spaces but not in general.
This one is the precise condition on X needed
for the evaluation map `C(X, Y) Г— X вҶ’ Y` to be continuous for all `Y`
when `C(X, Y)` is given the compact-open topology.

See also `WeaklyLocallyCompactSpace`, a typeclass that only assumes
that each point has a compact neighborhood. -/
class LocallyCompactSpace (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] : Prop where
  /-- In a locally compact space,
  every neighbourhood of every point contains a compact neighbourhood of that same point. -/
  local_compact_nhds : вҲҖ (x : X), вҲҖ n вҲҲ рқ“қ x, вҲғ s вҲҲ рқ“қ x, s вҠҶ n вҲ§ IsCompact s

/-- We say that `X` and `Y` are a locally compact pair of topological spaces,
if for any continuous map `f : X вҶ’ Y`, a point `x : X`, and a neighbourhood `s вҲҲ рқ“қ (f x)`,
there exists a compact neighbourhood `K вҲҲ рқ“қ x` such that `f` maps `K` to `s`.

This is a technical assumption that appears in several theorems,
most notably in `ContinuousMap.continuous_comp'` and `ContinuousMap.continuous_eval`.
It is satisfied in two cases:

- if `X` is a locally compact topological space, for obvious reasons;
- if `X` is a weakly locally compact topological space and `Y` is an RвӮҒ space;
  this fact is a simple generalization of the theorem
  saying that a weakly locally compact RвӮҒ topological space is locally compact.
-/
class LocallyCompactPair (X Y : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y] : Prop where
  /-- If `f : X вҶ’ Y` is a continuous map in a locally compact pair of topological spaces
  and `s : Set Y` is a neighbourhood of `f x`, `x : X`,
  then there exists a compact neighbourhood `K` of `x` such that `f` maps `K` to `s`. -/
  exists_mem_nhds_isCompact_mapsTo : вҲҖ {f : X вҶ’ Y} {x : X} {s : Set Y},
    Continuous f вҶ’ s вҲҲ рқ“қ (f x) вҶ’ вҲғ K вҲҲ рқ“қ x, IsCompact K вҲ§ Set.MapsTo f K s

export LocallyCompactPair (exists_mem_nhds_isCompact_mapsTo)

variable (X) in
/-- `Filter.cocompact` is the filter generated by complements to compact sets. -/
def Filter.cocompact : Filter X :=
  вЁ… (s : Set X) (_ : IsCompact s), рқ“ҹ sб¶ң

variable (X) in
/-- `Filter.coclosedCompact` is the filter generated by complements to closed compact sets.
In a Hausdorff space, this is the same as `Filter.cocompact`. -/
def Filter.coclosedCompact : Filter X :=
  вЁ… (s : Set X) (_ : IsClosed s) (_ : IsCompact s), рқ“ҹ sб¶ң
